 (IBA)gendereligibility rules.\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1029, \"end\": 1036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.999999957197816, \"rank\": 2.628906415717682e-08, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 1173, \"end\": 1178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998468511084, \"rank\": 1.531491169446901e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1269, \"end\": 1301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8125253491874872e-20, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1016}, {\"ngram\": \"women's boxing\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1085}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1119}, {\"ngram\": \"faced scrutiny\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"her participation\", \"from\": 1152, \"to\": 1169}, {\"ngram\": \"the Women's World Championships\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1242}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 25-year-old has always competed in the women's boxing divisionand has identified as female since birth.\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1442, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the women's boxing divisionand\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1404}, {\"ngram\": \"birth\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1441}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Harry Potter author Rowling was among the high-profile voices who spoke out against Khelif's participation against other female boxers.\", \"fro